<p><!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:paragraph --></p>
<p><strong>Corinna Schulenburg </strong>(Lead Organizer, <em>Polly</em>, she/her) is a trans artist and activist committed to ensemble practice and social justice.<em> </em>As a playwright, her work with Flux includes <em>Riding the Bull, Rue, Other Bodies, The Lesser Seductions of History, Jacob’s House, DEINDE</em>, <em>Honey Fist, Salvage,</em> <em>The Sea Concerto, </em>and <em>Operating Systems</em>. With Flux, she directed Ajax<em> in </em><em>Iraq </em>(NYITA nomination)<em>, A Midsummer Nights Dream</em>, and the Food:Souls <em>Goldsboro</em> and <em>Volleygirls. </em>As an actor with Flux, she has played Samantha in <em>Metra</em>, Max in <em>World Builders, </em>Dr. X in <em>Hearts Like Fists</em>, Ezekiel in <em>8 Little Antichrists</em> (NYITA nomination), and the Professor in <em>Rue.</em></p>
